Files:
- platform/plugin-sdk/src/storage.test.ts (add new describe blocks at end of file)

Context:
storage.test.ts covers: getLocalStorage, setLocalStorage, removeLocalStorage, findLocalStorageEntry (NONE), getSessionStorage, setSessionStorage, removeSessionStorage, getCookie, getAuthCache (NONE), setAuthCache (NONE), clearAuthCache (NONE), and an iframe fallback round-trip test.

The four missing functions are implemented in platform/plugin-sdk/src/storage.ts:

findLocalStorageEntry (lines ~70-98 of storage.ts):
  Iterates localStorage by index, calls predicate(key) on each, returns {key, value} for first match.
  Has iframe fallback identical to getLocalStorage: calls withIframeFallback() when storage is undefined.
  Inner function 'search' takes a Storage object and iterates it.

getAuthCache<T> (lines ~238-246):
  const ns = (globalThis as Record<string,unknown>).__openTabs as Record<string,unknown> | undefined;
  const cache = ns?.tokenCache as Record<string,unknown> | undefined;
  return (cache?.[namespace] as T) ?? null;
  — returns null if __openTabs or tokenCache is missing

setAuthCache<T> (lines ~253-261):
  Initializes __openTabs = {} if missing, tokenCache = {} if missing, then sets tokenCache[namespace] = value

clearAuthCache (lines ~267-273):
  Sets cache[namespace] = undefined (NOT delete cache[namespace])
  So after clearAuthCache('foo'), Object.keys(tokenCache) still includes 'foo' with value undefined
  getAuthCache returns null because undefined ?? null = null

Test structure to add:

// findLocalStorageEntry
describe('findLocalStorageEntry', () => {
  test('returns matching entry when predicate returns true'): set items in localStorage, call with predicate matching one key, expect {key, value}
  test('returns null when no entry matches'): no keys match predicate, expect null
  test('returns null when localStorage throws'): mock localStorage getter to throw SecurityError, expect null
  describe('iframe fallback', () => {
    test('returns value from iframe localStorage when localStorage is undefined'): same mock pattern as the getLocalStorage iframe fallback test (see lines 70-107 of storage.test.ts)
  })
})

// Auth cache
describe('getAuthCache', () => {
  // Set/restore g.__openTabs in each test
  test('returns value from tokenCache for known namespace')
  test('returns null when namespace is not in tokenCache')
  test('returns null when tokenCache is not initialized')
  test('returns null when __openTabs is not set')
})

describe('setAuthCache', () => {
  test('writes value to tokenCache')
  test('initializes __openTabs when missing')
  test('initializes tokenCache when __openTabs exists but tokenCache is missing')
  test('overwrites existing value')
})

describe('clearAuthCache', () => {
  test('getAuthCache returns null after clearAuthCache')
  test('key still exists in tokenCache with value undefined (not deleted)')
  test('no-op when cache namespace never set')
})

Constraints:
- Add tests at the end of storage.test.ts after the existing getCookie describe block
- Import findLocalStorageEntry, getAuthCache, setAuthCache, clearAuthCache from './storage.js' (add to existing import line at top)
- For auth cache tests: always clean up g.__openTabs in afterEach or per-test finally block (same pattern as config.test.ts which does 'delete g.__openTabs' in afterEach)
- For the iframe fallback test for findLocalStorageEntry: use the exact same spy pattern already used in the 'iframe fallback' describe blocks for getLocalStorage (lines 70-107). Mock document.createElement, document.body.appendChild, document.body.removeChild, and provide a mock contentWindow.localStorage with getItem and a mock length/key interface.
- Do NOT modify the existing tests — only add new ones
- The findLocalStorageEntry iframe mock needs to support length, key(i), and getItem(k) on the mock localStorage (since findLocalStorageEntry iterates by index). Contrast: getLocalStorage iframe mock only needs getItem.
